
[1]preparative

   PREPAR'ATIVE,a. Tending to prepare or make ready; having the power of
   preparing, qualifying or fitting for any thing; preparatory.

   He spent much time in quest of knowledge preparative to this work.

    PREPAR'ATIVE, n. That which has the power of preparing or previously
                 fitting for a purpose; that which prepares.

   Resolvedness in sin can with no reason be imagined a preparative to
   remission.

   1. That which is done to prevent an evil or secure some good.

   The miseries we suffer may be preparative of future blessings.

   2. Preparation; as, to make the necessary preparatives for a voyage.
